children.subject: Ah ok! My decal takes roughly 4-5 hours every week (including the lectures) and my breadth is around 3-4 hours too. Also, I don't mind math/proofs (tbh I do prefer them over programming assignments).

These are the exact classes I'm taking this semester haha, it's definitely a step up in terms of workload compared to the classes you're taking right now. 16B has similar homework difficulty with 16A but more time-consuming labs, 170 is a decent step up from 70 and so is 126. Assuming that your breadth and decal right now are pretty minimal, I'd expect that workload to be an increase over your current one (expect to spend a nontrivial amount of time on weekends).

Another thing to keep in mind is that you'll be taking 3 pset classes with little programming, so be prepared to do a lot of math/proofs and only math/proofs.
